stylometry: The problem with holding costs is that it is taking up space in the warehouse, store, etc. and that is wasting space which costs money.  Also, if you are producing some type of food or something that is perishable, it needs to be sold within a matter of time otherwise it needs to be thrown away.  The problem with production costs is that a consumer may need the product right away and if it is not ready they may find what they need elsewhere.  Either way, I think it would be better to have holding costs because producing everything at one time may save more money because producing in bulk is usually cheaper than producing a small number of products at a time.
